1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,900
=Episode 35=

19
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:41,000
I'd like to toast Comrade Yi Qin'e.

20
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,110
To be honest,

21
00:01:45,830 --> 00:01:48,000
my life before meeting Yi Qin'e

22
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
was completely aimless.

23
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:52,170
I didn't know
what the meaning of life was.

24
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:54,230
In the blink of an eye,

25
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,230
all these years just slipped away.

26
00:01:57,870 --> 00:01:58,710
But

27
00:02:00,670 --> 00:02:01,960
things are different now.

28
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:05,390
Ever since I met Comrade Yi Qin'e,

29
00:02:06,390 --> 00:02:09,240
my life has become so fulfilling.

30
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:13,150
Now, even eating a bowl of liangpi

31
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,240
makes me feel happy.

32
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:16,360
It tastes amazing.

33
00:02:17,790 --> 00:02:20,640
I wake up full of energy in the morning.

34
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,720
Qin'e,

35
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:26,430
you have

36
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,470
completely changed me.

37
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:34,280
You made me realize
what true happiness is.

38
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:38,790
I'm so moved.

39
00:02:38,790 --> 00:02:39,630
That was well said.

40
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:40,490
Great!

41
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:45,480
Well said, bro!

42
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,950
Getting sentimental here.

43
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,350
I don't really know what to say.

44
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:50,990
But

45
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:54,280
I hope to do better in the future.

46
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:55,760
I raise this glass

47
00:02:56,870 --> 00:02:58,430
to toast Comrade Qin'e.

48
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:02,320
Hongbing!

49
00:03:02,330 --> 00:03:04,480
Bro, are you proposing?

50
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,560
If you're proposing,

51
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:08,560
it's only romantic on one knee!

52
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,400
Get down on one knee!

53
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,240
Don't talk nonsense.

54
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:14,950
On one knee! On one knee!

55
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:15,790
Come on, get down!

56
00:03:15,790 --> 00:03:16,630
On one knee!

57
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:18,120
On one knee! On one knee!

58
00:03:18,430 --> 00:03:19,760
Fine, I'll kneel.

59
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:21,070
Qin'e! Qin'e!

60
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:25,430
Qin'e!

61
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:28,280
Qin'e!

62
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,500
(Restroom)

63
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:37,430
Qin'e! Qin'e!

64
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,920
Do you need to throw up?

65
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,510
What's going on?

66
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,280
It's empty in here.

67
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:52,030
(Diaojia Village)
Wang's roast chicken, spiced beef.

68
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:54,310
Let's eat and drink our fill today.

69
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,520
Sanyuan, what's this?

70
00:03:58,470 --> 00:04:01,150
Are you trying to bribe me with food?

71
00:04:01,590 --> 00:04:03,520
Why would I need to trick you?

72
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,120
Haven't you always wanted to hear

73
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,560
my thoughts on the new play?

74
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,430
None of that matters.

75
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,960
Aren't you heading back?

76
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,400
I just wanted to treat you today

77
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,710
to a nice meal and some drinks.

78
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,710
Say whatever you want.

79
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:20,360
Alright, sure.

80
00:04:23,590 --> 00:04:24,430
Excuse me, sir.

81
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,470
How do I get to Tian'anmen?

82
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,150
Miss.

83
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,680
You're from Chang'an Opera Troupe,
right?

84
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:35,150
You sound like you're
from Northwest China.

85
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,310
Tian'anmen? That's quite far.

86
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:40,080
Is it on the golden mountain?

87
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:40,920
What?

88
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:43,150
They say
it's on Beijing's golden mountain.

89
00:04:43,330 --> 00:04:44,840
There's no golden mountain in Beijing.

90
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,000
We only have Fragrant Hills.

91
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,840
If you're heading to Tian'anmen,

92
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,470
go this way.

93
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:52,590
Turn right outside the hostel
for the bus.

94
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,470
Take Bus Line 1 for seven stops.

95
00:04:54,470 --> 00:04:57,080
Get off at Tian'anmen East.

96
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Thank you, sir.

97
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,840
Wei Changsheng

98
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:04,310
brought Qinqiang opera to Beijing.

99
00:05:04,590 --> 00:05:05,560
The best part is

100
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:10,430
that he competed
with Kunqu opera in Beijing.

101
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,150
It's known as the Huabu
and Yabu rivalry.

102
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:17,120
Finally, Wei Changsheng staged Gun Lou.

103
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:22,910
Crowds flocked to Qinqiang troupes.

104
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:27,400
The Six Great Troupes
of the capital faded.

105
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:36,120
So, people started asking

106
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,280
how he did it.

107
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:41,360
Because Qinqiang opera is down-to-earth.

108
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,680
It has no deep historical allusions

109
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:48,520
or overly poetic lyrics.

110
00:05:49,630 --> 00:05:51,120
It's all about everyday life

111
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:53,120
and local slang.

112
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,430
It comes from the people

113
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,270
and goes to the people.

114
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,360
That's true vitality.

115
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:03,190
Well said.

116
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:04,030
Come on.

117
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,480
(Before going on stage tonight,)

118
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,270
(Yi Qin'e's hands are shaking.)

119
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,600
(But once the drums start,)

120
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:21,950
(she is no longer afraid.)

121
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:26,190
(The applause below no longer matters.)

122
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:29,390
(What matters is she's singing.)

123
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,950
(Chang'an Avenue is so wide;)

124
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:35,360
(the streetlights are so bright.)

125
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:39,830
(Finally, she brought opera to Beijing.)

126
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:47,620
(Long Live
the People's Republic of China)

127
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:13,510
Changing it isn't wrong.

128
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:16,560
It's true that Qinqiang opera

129
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:19,950
has always been sung
for the common people,

130
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,200
but

131
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,800
times have changed.

132
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:25,680
Qinqiang opera must change too.

133
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,310
But how do you change it?

134
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:29,560
You can't

135
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,270
just change the superficial aspects.

136
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:37,310
You're right.

137
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:38,920
It has to change.

138
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,000
Also, I need

139
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:50,040
a favor from you.

140
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,520
Go ahead.

141
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,720
Can you write a new play for Qin'e?

142
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:58,510
They just brought back the old plays.

143
00:07:58,510 --> 00:07:59,950
Who'd watch a new one?

144
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:03,920
Well, the old plays we have now

145
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,630
were once new plays too, right?

146
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,830
If you don't write new plays now,

147
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:12,720
what will they sing as old plays later?

148
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,950
Sanyuan,

149
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,750
you're absolutely right.

150
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,750
Old plays were once new.

151
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,350
Alright.

152
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,480
Then I'll write it.

153
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,800
I'll write an exclusive play

154
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,240
for Qin'e,

155
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,720
so whenever its name is mentioned,

156
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,390
they'll know it's her play.

157
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:38,800
Oh, Sanyuan.

158
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:42,040
Sooner or later, this world will become

159
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:44,070
something neither of us
can keep up with.

160
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,870
But I'll say it again:

161
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,160
No matter

162
00:08:49,390 --> 00:08:50,560
how you change,

163
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:53,070
as long as people of Qin live,

164
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,870
Qinqiang opera won't die.

165
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,160
With the Qinling Mountains here,

166
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:02,120
Qinqiang opera will survive.

167
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,270
(Many big things happened that year.)

168
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,600
(The wanted Wei Zhenhai)

169
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,600
(was finally caught in Chang'an.)

170
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:20,040
(The citywide uproar finally ended.)

171
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:23,190
(Good News)
(The people of Qin shined in Beijing.)

172
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:26,160
(Listen to Qinqiang Opera)
(The Qinqiang opera was popular.)

173
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:28,620
(Qinchuan Qinqiang Opera Theater)

174
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:32,980
(Congrats to Yi Qin'e on Her Transfer
into the Province)

175
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,940
(And Winning National First Prize)

176
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,700
(And Winning National First Prize)

177
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,830
(The train rumbled south.)

178
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,310
(Time is money)
(Shenzhen built fast.)

179
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,560
(Early 90s)
(Everyone went into business.)

180
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,600
(It seemed like everywhere)

181
00:09:49,070 --> 00:09:51,070
(was full of money and chances.)

182
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:56,260
(Congrats on the Art Theater's Division)

183
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:58,510
(The provincial troupe had a reform.)

184
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,830
(The province wanted stars to lead.)

185
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,800
(Yi Qin'e couldn't decline it)

186
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:06,000
(and became the Youth Troupe Leader.)

187
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,720
(The troupe's new housing was built.)

188
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,030
(Everyone's living environment)

189
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:15,030
(Housing Handover)
(changed from the tube-shaped)

190
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:16,820
(apartment buildings to flats.)

191
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:17,670
(Xishi Tofu Shop)

192
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:19,910
(Those who got houses were overjoyed.)

193
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,790
(Qin Bawa focused
on writing a new play,)

194
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:27,440
(wondering if it could beat
the rock noise.)

195
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,320
(Times have changed;)

196
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:30,870
(people have changed too.)

197
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,390
(But as long as the curtain rises,)

198
00:10:34,630 --> 00:10:35,750
(with the lights up,)

199
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:39,440
(the show must go on.)

200
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:43,500
(The End)

201
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:52,080
♪In the crowd, there are you and me♪

202
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:55,840
♪Meeting, knowing,
figuring each other out♪

203
00:10:56,560 --> 00:11:00,160
♪In the crowd, it is you and me♪

204
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,840
♪Pretending to be decent with a smile♪

205
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,930
♪No need to say too much♪

206
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:06,840
How is it?

207
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,200
What?

208
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,750
Awesome, right?

209
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:13,000
Boom-cha-cha is out of style now.

210
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,630
This is the hottest trend.

211
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,030
Do you know what this is?

212
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,120
Rock and roll.

213
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,480
If you ask me,

214
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:23,200
this was just copied
from the Qinqiang opera's

215
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,720
painted-face role.

216
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,920
♪Just as charming, just as beautiful♪

217
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:30,790
Are you deaf from all this noise?

218
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:32,270
If you can't stand it, let's go.

219
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,630
Let's listen; it's good.

220
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,750
Really?

221
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,080
Listen, then.

222
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,960
♪You know♪

223
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:42,880
♪What we really want to do♪

224
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,480
♪Don't care too much♪

225
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,120
♪And don't be sad♪

226
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,010
♪One day you'll leave me♪

227
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,630
Why are you looking at this?

228
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,790
Look at this.

229
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,030
505.

230
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:01,390
Give me one.

231
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,720
Exact same recipe as 505.

232
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,720
What is this?

233
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:06,870
It's only a fifth of the price.

234
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:07,960
Come on, give me one.

235
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,790
A great deal for yourself or as a gift.

236
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,390
Here, take a look.

237
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:13,320
This looks pretty legit.

238
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,160
I'll take one.

239
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,670
I was wondering what to get my nephew.

240
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,770
He's starting middle school.

241
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:17,630
This will be perfect.

242
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,080
Just get a few more.

243
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:21,240
Your future kids can use them too.

244
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,320
Will it still be useful
when they grow up?

245
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:24,310
Seriously.

246
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,210
What? Come on.

247
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,340
- 30% off for you.
- Enough!

248
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:27,440
30% off, 30% off!

249
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:29,480
Take it, take it.

250
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:30,870
Come on, have one more.

251
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,200
Wang Qinsheng, what are you doing?

252
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,480
Is this rehearsal room a flea market?

253
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:36,870
Director Feng.

254
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:39,110
Director Feng,

255
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:40,720
my buddy has this Kombucha.

256
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,890
It's perfect for people like you.

257
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:43,900
What kind of person am I?

258
00:12:43,910 --> 00:12:44,680
You know.

259
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,790
You've been stressed for years,

260
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:47,840
always wearing a frown.

261
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,870
Let me help you relax.

262
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:51,600
You're exactly right.

263
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,510
- Director Feng.
- You make me frown.

264
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,920
Director Feng.

265
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,080
This is...

266
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,110
- Mr. Qin.
- Hello.

267
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,670
I'm Feng Zi, Director of the troupe.

268
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:02,000
Come on, everyone, stand up.

269
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:03,320
No need, Director Feng.

270
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,160
Please, don't stand.

271
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:07,720
Just make yourselves comfortable.

272
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,390
No need to stand up.

273
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,630
Let me introduce him to you all.

274
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,550
Today, we're very honored to have

275
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:16,240
the famous Qinqiang opera playwright,

276
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,900
- Mr. Qin Bawa.
- Great!

277
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:19,000
Let's welcome Mr. Qin Bawa

278
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,240
to share a few words with us.

279
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:22,840
He spent a whole year pouring his heart

280
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,320
into writing this new piece,

281
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,790
Hu Xian Jie,

282
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:28,790
which is also our upcoming play.

283
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:29,750
Is that okay?

284
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,270
Yes!

285
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:33,510
Hello, everyone.

286
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,870
Regarding Hu Xian Jie,

287
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:39,200
some might feel it's distant from us.

288
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:41,550
It tells the story of a fox,

289
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:44,750
but it's actually not distant at all.

290
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,510
- Let's sit and talk.
- Okay.

291
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,750
Because in Hu Xian Jie,

292
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:51,030
the main character,

293
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:55,840
a fox spirit from the deep mountains,

294
00:13:56,600 --> 00:14:00,360
has been cultivating in the wilderness.

295
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:02,750
Her talent led her to enlightenment,

296
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,480
but knowing nothing of the human world,

297
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,200
she feels confused.

298
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:12,150
She's lost between friendship and love,

299
00:14:13,030 --> 00:14:14,000
just like

300
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,550
Prometheus or Sisyphus

301
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:17,790
in Greek mythology.

302
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,270
She is

303
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:23,510
a tragic figure full of idealism.

304
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,320
Her entire life

305
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:31,390
is about exploring, seeking,
and choosing.

306
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:34,240
I see the script has been given to you.

307
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,390
Next,

308
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:38,390
it's your creation.

309
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,600
Yes, exactly.

310
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:43,790
Everyone, let's explore together

311
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,720
the long journey of the fox.

312
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:50,320
Great, great.

313
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,670
Mr. Qin,

314
00:14:53,150 --> 00:14:54,390
I've read the script.

315
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:57,390
May I share some thoughts?

316
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:02,440
In this script,

317
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:05,390
it says people are greedy and blind.

318
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:06,990
But I think

319
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:09,720
that it's the reform and opening-up era.

320
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,320
It advocates for some to get rich first.

321
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,840
So, I was wondering this:

322
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:16,270
Does the script try

323
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,720
to lamb paste the world too much?

324
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,080
Lambaste.

325
00:15:21,510 --> 00:15:22,350
Baste what?

326
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:24,320
The word is lambaste.

327
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:27,480
It means to severely criticize.

328
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,080
Everyone, don't laugh at him.

329
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:29,950
Stop laughing, guys.

330
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:30,870
Don't mind them, sir.

331
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:32,320
What kind of question is that?

332
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,160
Your question...

333
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:34,440
No, no. Director Feng.

334
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,320
It's a great point.

335
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,600
Come up to the front. Come on.

336
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:38,630
Come here.

337
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:41,590
I like it.

338
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,950
I'd love to discuss things

339
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,390
with you all.

340
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:47,550
Sit.

341
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,840
Don't be shy.

342
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:50,320
You were right to ask.

343
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,720
You asked this question

344
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:52,720
from a different angle.

345
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,120
You're different, but that's normal.

346
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,720
I don't think it's a condemnation.

347
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,030
Let me ask you about Jia Baoyu.

348
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:01,630
Would you say he's affectionate

349
00:16:02,510 --> 00:16:03,630
or heartless?

350
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:07,550
It depends on perspectives.

351
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:08,840
Exactly.

352
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:11,360
Most readers think Jia Baoyu

353
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,200
is affectionate.

354
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,200
He's romantic, right?

355
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,320
Right, right.

356
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:17,360
But from Xue Baochai's perspective,

357
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,910
he showed her no affection
at all, right?

358
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:21,150
Right, exactly.

359
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:24,120
So, your angle on this question
is great.

360
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:27,000
If you want to better understand

361
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,120
my script,

362
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,320
you need to read more.

363
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,080
Not just myths and legends,

364
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,840
but also ancient poetry.

365
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,510
Because when I wrote this play's lyrics,

366
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:40,200
I referenced the poems
of great Tang Dynasty poets,

367
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,270
such as Li Bai, Cui Hu, and Li Shangyin.

368
00:17:00,910 --> 00:17:01,750
Stop.

369
00:17:01,870 --> 00:17:02,710
Stop dancing.

370
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,840
Rehearsing this is worse
than trading stocks.

371
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:09,840
At least stocks have ups and downs.

372
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:11,510
Look at you guys.

373
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:13,630
One note from start to finish.

374
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,200
We're done for today.

375
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,840
You can't blame us.

376
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:19,000
There's not even a single drumbeat.

377
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:20,440
Just a tape recorder.

378
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,280
Is it my fault?

379
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:22,870
Guo Chuizi took time off.

380
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,670
The Youth Troupe took our lead drummer.

381
00:17:25,840 --> 00:17:27,390
Troupe Leader Yi gave the word,

382
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:29,720
and they swept away all our best stuff.

383
00:17:29,870 --> 00:17:31,030
They're working hard,

384
00:17:31,030 --> 00:17:32,270
rehearsing, and making money.

385
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,280
And look at us,

386
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,000
just hanging around here half-dead.

387
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:38,870
Jiahe,

388
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,600
isn't Troupe Leader Yi your classmate?

389
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,550
She didn't even look out for us.

390
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:45,670
That's uncool. Go talk to her.

391
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:47,000
Enough, you guys.

392
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,550
Don't blame your tools for a bad job.

393
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,630
You lack skill, so you blame the drum?

394
00:17:51,030 --> 00:17:53,080
Director Dang, not trading stocks today?

395
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,440
What's wrong? Did you lose money?

396
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,790
What do you know about stocks?

397
00:17:58,630 --> 00:17:59,470
Let me tell you.

398
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,600
It's incredibly thrilling.

399
00:18:01,670 --> 00:18:02,600
You know what?

400
00:18:02,910 --> 00:18:05,030
I stayed at that market

401
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:06,360
all day yesterday.

402
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,790
It was so incredibly crowded.

403
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,000
You'd think there was a festival.

404
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:12,600
How about I take you there

405
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:13,790
in a few days?

406
00:18:13,910 --> 00:18:15,360
Acting is just like that.

407
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,480
With the exact same role,

408
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,200
your act and his would just...

409
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:19,770
Director Feng, are we about done?

410
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:20,620
Can we call it a day?

411
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:21,960
Sure, sure. You can go.

412
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,240
We're done for today.

413
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,000
Feel free to leave if you need to.

414
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,840
Alright, I'm taking off.

415
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,560
Thank you. Thanks.

416
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:30,910
Mr. Qin, I'm a huge fan.

417
00:18:31,030 --> 00:18:33,120
Mr. Qin, this is Xue Guisheng,

418
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,630
a Xiaosheng transferred

419
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:36,240
from Tianshui, Gansu.

420
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,000
A student of Su Yumin.

421
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,000
Yes, exactly.

422
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:40,710
Nice to meet you.

423
00:18:40,740 --> 00:18:41,630
Hello, Mr. Qin.

424
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:42,480
Mr. Qin,

425
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,830
could I get your autograph?

426
00:18:43,830 --> 00:18:44,720
Why?

427
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:45,880
I'm not a big star.

428
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,920
Come on, you're a great artist.

429
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,720
Yeah, write a message for the youth.

430
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,000
It'd be very meaningful.

431
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:52,590
Is that okay?

432
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,320
Alright then.

433
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:57,390
You're a Xiaosheng?

434
00:18:57,390 --> 00:18:58,640
Xiaosheng, yes.

435
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,960
I'm so lucky today.

436
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:02,640
Indeed.

437
00:19:04,030 --> 00:19:05,960
(Hu Xian Jie)
Nice handwriting.

438
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:07,570
(Waste no time)
You distract me.

439
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,240
- That's true.
- Done.

440
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:10,480
Very good, very good.

441
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,350
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

442
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,790
Elegant scholar,

443
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,750
do not decay.

444
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:18,110
Waste no time.

445
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,000
Where did all your studying go?

446
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:22,830
It's an uncommon word.

447
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,440
Read more, read more ancient poems.

448
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:26,500
Okay, okay.

449
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:27,360
Mr. Qin.

450
00:19:27,370 --> 00:19:28,240
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

451
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:29,550
Thanks, thank you.

452
00:19:29,550 --> 00:19:30,390
Troupe Leader.

453
00:19:30,790 --> 00:19:32,640
Thank you for your support.

454
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:34,440
I've been meaning
to treat you to a meal.

455
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:35,980
The last time you came,

456
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,220
we went to Beijing for a show.

457
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,080
- Yes.
- Right.

458
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:40,200
Sir, I wasn't asking you to host me.

459
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:43,030
I really did it for the play.

460
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:44,680
Now, you've paid me the writing fee.

461
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:46,000
I've said my piece on the play.

462
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:46,930
My job is done.

463
00:19:46,950 --> 00:19:47,850
- Thanks.
- Okay, bye.

464
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:48,670
No, no.

465
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,590
You should stay for a few more days.

466
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:53,400
Aren't we partnered

467
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,680
with Tangcheng Hotel?

468
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:56,310
- Yes.
- Let Mr. Qin stay there.

469
00:19:56,310 --> 00:19:58,200
- Okay.
- No, no, no need.

470
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,240
I'm used to being free.

471
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,240
I've already picked a place.

472
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:03,390
Goodbye.

473
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:04,920
- Let it go.
- Please, let it be.

474
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:05,830
I'll walk him out.

475
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:07,400
- Okay.
- Goodbye, Mr. Qin.

476
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,680
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

477
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:10,910
Yeah.

478
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,030
We've paid him?

479
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:12,870
Yes.

480
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,880
He's explained the play?

481
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:14,960
He explained it perfectly.

482
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,000
That's good.

483
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,830
Troupe Leader, look what Mr. Qin wrote.

484
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,160
Elegant scholar,

485
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:22,920
waste no time.

486
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:23,870
Right.

487
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:27,110
Why didn't Mr. Qin give me an autograph?

488
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,200
I'll sign one for you.

489
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,440
Why would I want yours?

490
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,920
Mr. Qin! Mr. Qin!

491
00:20:33,590 --> 00:20:34,430
Always peeing!

492
00:20:34,590 --> 00:20:36,440
The whole yard reeks of pee!

493
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,720
Do you know where we are?

494
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,060
This is the provincial capital.

495
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:41,880
Day in and day out!

496
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,960
Have you got a prostate problem?
Always peeing!

497
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:45,150
You want to pee?

498
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,920
Do you know how hard I work all day?

499
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:49,070
Pee, pee, pee!

500
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:50,750
Why not pee on your mom's Kang?

501
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:51,800
Let me tell you!

502
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:54,310
Mr. Qin, why do you live here?

503
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:56,480
It's great here.

504
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:57,480
It's full of life.

505
00:20:58,030 --> 00:20:59,750
To truly understand Chang'an locals...

506
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:00,590
This way.

507
00:21:01,310 --> 00:21:03,070
You have to come here

508
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:03,910
to look

509
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:05,190
and listen.

510
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,550
You must live here.

511
00:21:06,550 --> 00:21:07,480
Did you see that woman?

512
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:08,640
She isn't

513
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,240
from Chang'an.

514
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:12,790
She must've married in from out of town

515
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:13,630
just a few years ago.

516
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,750
How do you know?

517
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:18,000
A true Chang'an native

518
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,110
wouldn't emphasize it.

519
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:20,240
"I'm from the city."

520
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,550
"I'm from Chang'an."

521
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:22,960
"I'm from Qinchuan."

522
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,550
That just loses confidence.

523
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,790
Did you hear what she said

524
00:21:26,790 --> 00:21:28,070
in a panic?

525
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:30,720
Those words like Kang?

526
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:32,880
That's not local in Chang'an.

527
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:36,960
Language...

528
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,070
A person's experiences

529
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:39,440
are all hidden in their words.

530
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:42,240
That right there is folk language.

531
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:45,830
Grounded and solid.

532
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:48,030
Full of charm and so powerful.

533
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,480
I've never been

534
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,400
up to the City Wall.

535
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:02,390
Let's go.

536
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:03,350
Let's go take a look.

537
00:22:05,830 --> 00:22:07,440
It's so wide up here.

538
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,030
You could even drive a car on it.

539
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,550
You've never been here before?

540
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:12,760
No.

541
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,240
Ever since I came,

542
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:16,110
I've just been focused on performing.

543
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:18,110
Mr. Qin,

544
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,640
your new script is truly amazing.

545
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,510
I feel like it was written for me.

546
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:25,750
It has so many things I want to say.

547
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:27,190
It's just...

548
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:29,070
How should I put it?

549
00:22:29,850 --> 00:22:30,700
I...

550
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,110
I don't know how to explain it.

551
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:35,680
I'll definitely perform this play well.

552
00:22:35,830 --> 00:22:36,720
Take it easy.

553
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:39,590
By the way,
I haven't congratulated you yet.

554
00:22:40,110 --> 00:22:42,000
In the years since you came to Chang'an,

555
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:43,350
you've achieved so much.

556
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:45,640
You've become a star

557
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:47,400
and the deputy troupe leader.

558
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:49,720
You've really made it.

559
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:52,400
I don't really care about all that.

560
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:54,400
Besides, I don't know anything else.

561
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:56,110
I just focus on performing well.

562
00:22:57,030 --> 00:22:59,030
Fame and fortune are funny like that.

563
00:22:59,510 --> 00:23:00,550
When you ignore them,

564
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:02,110
they come looking for you instead.

565
00:23:02,910 --> 00:23:04,000
But you need to be careful.

566
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:07,350
Don't let fame drag you down.

567
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,270
Your hardships and obstacles won't be

568
00:23:12,790 --> 00:23:15,590
singing, reciting, acting,
or acrobatic fighting.

569
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,720
You need to be mentally prepared.

570
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:18,790
Prepared for what?

571
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,480
Well...

572
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,200
That varies from person to person.

573
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:28,550
I really can't tell you.

574
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:31,120
You have to figure it out
and experience it

575
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,350
on your own.

576
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:34,750
If you figure it out,

577
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:36,640
you'll make it.

578
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,110
Here are the receipts
from the past few days.

579
00:23:45,110 --> 00:23:46,000
Take a look at this.

580
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,800
Here's the plan.

581
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:55,960
After finishing eating,

582
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:58,400
have your guys buy the paint.

583
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,440
Okay, sure, no problem.

584
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,590
Look over here.

585
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,960
Welcome home.

586
00:24:23,550 --> 00:24:25,030
Come in and take a look.

587
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:26,640
See how I set up the new place.

588
00:24:27,830 --> 00:24:29,030
I cleaned up everything

589
00:24:29,030 --> 00:24:30,110
that I possibly could.

590
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,510
Here, let me take your bag.

591
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,350
Feel free to look around.

592
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:36,270
The lighting in here is great.

593
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:39,720
I went to Zhuque Gate this morning

594
00:24:40,110 --> 00:24:41,880
and happened to pass the flower market,

595
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:45,000
so I brought this pot of flowers back.

596
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:46,960
Don't they look fresh?

597
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:52,400
They smell amazing.

598
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:53,480
Come on.

599
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,720
Here, put your slippers on.

600
00:24:54,790 --> 00:24:56,110
I'll put your shoes right here.

601
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,310
You must be exhausted from work.

602
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,270
How was work today? Did it go well?

603
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:02,350
Have some warm water.

604
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,830
A banana full of love.

605
00:25:04,830 --> 00:25:07,830
Qin Town's Mipi and Laozao.

606
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,240
Come on, take a bite.

607
00:25:17,270 --> 00:25:20,920
Your favorite soup dumplings.

608
00:25:22,070 --> 00:25:23,960
I got them at Huimin Street
this morning.

609
00:25:24,110 --> 00:25:25,400
Come on, have a taste.

610
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:29,550
Li Huiniang's eyes are so expressive.

611
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:30,960
I'll hang it up.

612
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,280
Liang,

613
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:46,510
you're amazing.

614
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,000
This is

615
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:48,960
Toshiba.

616
00:25:50,030 --> 00:25:50,960
How much was it, bro?

617
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,070
It's nothing.

618
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,240
Over two thousand.

619
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:54,150
It's nothing.

620
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:58,250
It's this unit, 201.

621
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:00,030
- Got it!
- Handle it with care!

622
00:26:00,070 --> 00:26:02,030
Especially the speakers,
over 7,000 yuan.

623
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,070
What speakers cost over 7,000 yuan?

624
00:26:04,070 --> 00:26:05,000
They're imported.

625
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:06,840
Lili.

626
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,640
This sofa feels amazing.

627
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:10,680
How much is it? Let me get one too.

628
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,640
You can't afford it; it's custom.

629
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,730
- Give me a hand!
- Sir!

630
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:15,270
Can this sofa fit through the hall?

631
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,400
I have a piano too.

632
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,070
A custom-made Yamaha.

633
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,080
Slow down, slow down!

634
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,280
So, this piano is

635
00:26:20,290 --> 00:26:21,640
just like our Biangbiang noodles.

636
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:23,350
It has to be freshly made.

637
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:24,590
Shut up.

638
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,110
You know nothing about art. So tacky.

639
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:26,960
Take it easy.

640
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,830
Fine, I'm a bumpkin.

641
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,720
How about this?

642
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:29,680
Bring me along with you.

643
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,640
The clothing business
seems very lucrative.

644
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,720
Why do I even bother doing flips, right?

645
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:34,920
You're destined to do flips.

646
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,510
- Slow down.
- Let's go, sir.

647
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:37,580
I'll get the door for you.

648
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,320
- Liang.
- What?

649
00:26:39,350 --> 00:26:41,110
The clothing business is so lucrative?

650
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,350
Lili is just that capable.

651
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,200
Sometimes, I even feel

652
00:26:45,750 --> 00:26:46,960
like I'm a kept man.

653
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:47,800
Bro,

654
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,830
are you sure she's selling clothes?

655
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,200
At Luoma Market, running a stall.

656
00:26:55,630 --> 00:26:57,310
You little brat,
I'll tear your mouth off!

657
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,400
Don't you know what she sells?

658
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,240
Alright, bro.

659
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:02,240
This jerk.

660
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:05,790
You think you're amazing?

661
00:27:06,070 --> 00:27:07,480
You just sell clothes.

662
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,070
A self-employed entrepreneur.

663
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:11,640
Why act all high and mighty?

664
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:12,960
So full of yourself.

665
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:13,960
Right, Qin'e?

666
00:27:14,030 --> 00:27:15,160
(Over the past year,)

667
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:18,240
(nothing has changed
between Yi Qin'e and Liu Hongbing.)

668
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,590
(No progress.)

669
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:23,270
- (Liu Hongbing hasn't backed off.)
- What's wrong?

670
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:25,350
- (He's still devoted,)
- You were fine.

671
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,920
(running errands,)

672
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:28,750
- (and buying things.)
- Qin'e.

673
00:27:29,830 --> 00:27:31,600
- (Yi Qin'e has)
- What's wrong?

674
00:27:31,610 --> 00:27:33,610
- Do you have other business?
- (mixed feelings.)

675
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,520
My business

676
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:35,590
is looking after you.

677
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,550
Then just leave.

678
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,310
What's the fuss about?

679
00:27:40,790 --> 00:27:42,070
Aren't I helping you right now?

680
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,270
I told you we're not right
for each other.

681
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,510
I didn't say we were a match either.

682
00:27:55,070 --> 00:27:57,000
Stop pestering me here, alright?

683
00:27:58,310 --> 00:27:59,920
Don't you still need my help?

684
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,000
You just moved here.

685
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,960
If I weren't here helping you decorate,

686
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:05,310
you'd work yourself to the bone.

687
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,000
Don't worry.

688
00:28:07,070 --> 00:28:08,920
I'll leave once I'm done here.

689
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:12,110
Here, wipe this.

690
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,400
You're helping me?

691
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:21,740
You...

692
00:28:21,790 --> 00:28:22,630
What are you doing?

693
00:28:22,860 --> 00:28:23,840
- Qin'e.
- Give it here.

694
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:24,760
What?

695
00:28:24,770 --> 00:28:25,710
The keys.

696
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:31,680
The custom rug and sofa
will be delivered

697
00:28:32,350 --> 00:28:33,720
to the door in a few days.

698
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,920
Once I set them all up for you,

699
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:37,040
I'll leave.

700
00:28:37,100 --> 00:28:39,350
Change the locks
if you don't believe me.

701
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:57,310
I need to go to Beishan in a few days.

702
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:58,880
It won't be long.

703
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:01,560
Don't miss me too much.

704
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:16,270
♪I am Bai Yunxian♪

705
00:29:16,270 --> 00:29:17,590
♪Miss Bai♪

706
00:29:18,790 --> 00:29:23,240
(Youth Troupe)
♪Mr. Xu, where do you live♪

707
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:31,880
♪My family has lived in Qiantang County
for generations♪

708
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:43,000
♪My name is Xu Xian♪

709
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,350
♪What do you do for a living♪

710
00:29:48,310 --> 00:29:49,160
It tastes strong.

711
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:52,480
Comrade Yi Qin'e from your troupe

712
00:29:53,480 --> 00:29:56,550
has all the acting talent in the world.

713
00:29:56,550 --> 00:29:58,680
Thank you for caring about Qin'e.

714
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:01,550
The development of Qinqiang opera

715
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:03,750
really needs your strong support.

716
00:30:03,750 --> 00:30:04,680
Yes, absolutely.

717
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,550
Why isn't Yi Qin'e here yet?

718
00:30:08,510 --> 00:30:09,350
Yeah.

719
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:12,590
She'll be right here.

720
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,190
Let's drink with Chief Hu first.

721
00:30:14,190 --> 00:30:15,050
Pour the drinks.

722
00:30:15,070 --> 00:30:15,910
Come on, come on.

723
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:16,770
Okay, okay.

724
00:30:28,310 --> 00:30:29,270
Xue Guisheng,

725
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:31,880
how long has it been since you showered?

726
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:33,400
Do you know you smell awful?

727
00:30:34,030 --> 00:30:36,240
That's nonsense. It's not me.

728
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:37,520
What nonsense?

729
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,510
The wind is blowing from the east.

730
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:41,160
It blew all your stench over here.

731
00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:42,790
Don't think I don't know.

732
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,240
They all said they've never seen you

733
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,720
shower in the troupe's bathhouse.

734
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:46,750
And you still deny it?

735
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:48,790
Impossible. Smell it.

736
00:30:48,790 --> 00:30:51,110
What are you doing? It stinks!

737
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,480
It can't possibly be me.

738
00:30:57,550 --> 00:30:59,070
I just showered last week.

739
00:31:00,190 --> 00:31:01,040
Qin'e.

740
00:31:01,070 --> 00:31:02,030
Why laugh? Seriously.

741
00:31:04,310 --> 00:31:05,150
Qin'e.

742
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:06,350
Look.

743
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,750
Jiahe is the lead now.

744
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,550
You're a big star too.

745
00:31:11,070 --> 00:31:13,440
Let me play Qing next.

746
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,680
We're both from Ningzhou.

747
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:17,590
I'm no worse than Zhu Hanmei.

748
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,310
You've taken too much time off lately.

749
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:22,240
They already cast Zhu Hanmei.

750
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,310
There's nothing I can do.

751
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:26,160
Don't ask. I got scammed.

752
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,240
What happened?

753
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:30,960
Weren't you dating someone?

754
00:31:31,270 --> 00:31:32,310
I saw your boyfriend.

755
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:33,960
When are you getting married?

756
00:31:34,110 --> 00:31:35,790
He was a total scammer.

757
00:31:36,310 --> 00:31:37,880
He said his dad could get me a job

758
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:40,000
in the Provincial Bureau of Culture,

759
00:31:40,310 --> 00:31:42,590
but his dad is just
a Provincial Party Committee guard.

760
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:44,720
What a waste of my time.

761
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,590
Slow down! Slow down!

762
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,920
Qin'e, why are you still sitting here?

763
00:31:50,510 --> 00:31:51,350
Go get up there.

764
00:31:51,350 --> 00:31:52,510
The leaders are all waiting.

765
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:55,000
Troupe Leader, ask someone else.

766
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:56,350
Who else can I ask?

767
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:57,920
You're the deputy troupe leader now.

768
00:31:58,510 --> 00:32:00,640
Hosting leaders is part of your job.

769
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:03,920
Then I quit.

770
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,350
You quit? Who will take over then?

771
00:32:05,350 --> 00:32:06,190
I'll do it.

772
00:32:06,790 --> 00:32:07,630
I can do it.

773
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,760
Let me do it.

774
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:09,920
What could you do?

775
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,160
Tell me what you want.

776
00:32:12,310 --> 00:32:13,160
I need some time off.

777
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,270
You're just causing trouble.

778
00:32:16,270 --> 00:32:18,270
You just think the troupe underpays you.

779
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:19,110
Right?

780
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:20,480
You're the troupe leader.

781
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:21,880
Tell me. Is my pay low or not?

782
00:32:22,350 --> 00:32:23,240
It's not low at all.

783
00:32:23,790 --> 00:32:25,110
The troupe's rule is based

784
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,880
on years of experience and ability.

785
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:28,070
I meet both, right?

786
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:30,070
I joined at 14.

787
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:32,070
First Wusheng role, then Chou role.

788
00:32:32,070 --> 00:32:33,640
After Erhu, I learned Banhu.

789
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,030
From small gong to big gong,

790
00:32:35,030 --> 00:32:36,480
I finally sat at the drum set.

791
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,550
I'm our troupe's drummer.

792
00:32:38,550 --> 00:32:41,720
Fans call me the Northwest Drum King.

793
00:32:42,110 --> 00:32:43,790
Maybe I didn't make great feats,

794
00:32:43,790 --> 00:32:44,960
but I put in the hard work.

795
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:46,680
A young girl from another county

796
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:47,520
even got a raise.

797
00:32:47,530 --> 00:32:48,750
Why is there none for me?

798
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:50,720
The provincial leaders appointed her

799
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,640
as the deputy troupe leader.

800
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:53,640
Who do you think you are?

801
00:32:54,590 --> 00:32:56,720
I can't even argue with you on that.

802
00:32:57,310 --> 00:32:58,640
I'll tell Troupe Leader Yi, then.

803
00:32:59,070 --> 00:32:59,910
Troupe Leader Yi,

804
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,550
after tonight's performance,

805
00:33:01,550 --> 00:33:03,310
I won't perform. I'm taking a leave.

806
00:33:05,030 --> 00:33:06,240
What a troublemaker.

807
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,160
I'll deal with you later.

808
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,640
Qin'e, you should go up.

809
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,080
Zhou.

810
00:33:36,550 --> 00:33:37,960
Come on, let's switch seats.

811
00:33:46,270 --> 00:33:47,240
You must be tired.

812
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:50,400
You just started out.

813
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:53,310
You'll face many awful people
and things.

814
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:54,280
Take your time.

815
00:33:57,270 --> 00:33:59,270
Dealing with plays is relatively easy.

816
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:01,550
You'll succeed if you work hard.

817
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:06,590
Dealing with people is too hard.

818
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:07,830
Look, look.

819
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:10,350
You figured it out in just two days.

820
00:34:12,590 --> 00:34:13,430
Troupe Leader,

821
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:14,910
I really think

822
00:34:14,910 --> 00:34:16,440
I'm not cut out for this deputy role.

823
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:18,960
Who said that?

824
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:20,000
Look at you now.

825
00:34:20,020 --> 00:34:21,590
You're managing both troupes so well.

826
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:24,440
Yang Pai Feng
is already showing results.

827
00:34:24,640 --> 00:34:26,510
The person you recommended is great too.

828
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:28,750
Chu Jiahe really has some solid skills.

829
00:34:29,070 --> 00:34:29,920
Keep it down.

830
00:34:30,030 --> 00:34:32,070
I don't want anyone
to know I referred her.

831
00:34:32,830 --> 00:34:34,350
I haven't told a soul.

832
00:34:34,680 --> 00:34:37,440
But Director Ding recommended her too.

833
00:34:39,240 --> 00:34:42,000
Troupe Leaders, I need a word with you.

834
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,440
Wang Qinsheng

835
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:45,830
hasn't shown up for over a week.

836
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,510
Hu Xian Jie

837
00:34:47,510 --> 00:34:50,240
can't depend on him.

838
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,550
See who can fill in for him

839
00:34:52,640 --> 00:34:54,030
and run a scene with you.

840
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:04,440
The one reading the book, right?

841
00:35:07,070 --> 00:35:08,680
We're on the same page.

842
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,640
I didn't say a word.

843
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:13,480
I didn't say a word either.

844
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:15,720
From now on, we'll give up

845
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:16,880
on the picky ones.

846
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,070
The show is everything, right?

847
00:35:21,590 --> 00:35:22,430
Qin'e,

848
00:35:23,070 --> 00:35:25,110
if there's any mess from now on,

849
00:35:25,110 --> 00:35:26,350
I'll take the heat for you.

850
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:28,510
You just need to focus

851
00:35:28,510 --> 00:35:30,200
and do your job well.

852
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,400
In the future,

853
00:35:37,750 --> 00:35:38,920
we'll work together.

854
00:35:39,590 --> 00:35:41,000
With me here,

855
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,350
just rest easy and sing.

856
00:35:51,630 --> 00:35:52,590
What are you doing?

857
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,440
This is a clinic.

858
00:35:57,230 --> 00:35:59,400
Don't make it look like a shady salon.

859
00:35:59,510 --> 00:36:00,350
This is embarrassing.

860
00:36:00,710 --> 00:36:02,760
No rush, I'm not done yet.

861
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:04,960
See how this feels.

862
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:06,280
Does it look good?

863
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:08,590
You really are a genius.

864
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,000
We need to change our mindset.

865
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:15,030
Do you know what's trendy now?

866
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:18,030
Wellness and health care.

867
00:36:20,190 --> 00:36:21,280
We can't just rely

868
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,440
on people with leg issues coming to you.

869
00:36:23,590 --> 00:36:25,230
We need to get healthy people

870
00:36:25,230 --> 00:36:26,070
to walk in here too.

871
00:36:26,630 --> 00:36:28,070
Illness is a very abstract concept.

872
00:36:28,550 --> 00:36:29,590
Back in the tough times,

873
00:36:29,590 --> 00:36:30,800
bleeding didn't mean illness.

874
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:32,670
Now that life is better,

875
00:36:33,230 --> 00:36:35,190
even feeling a bit down

876
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:36,230
is considered an illness.

877
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,550
I get it now.

878
00:36:39,590 --> 00:36:42,550
From now on, we treat the sick

879
00:36:42,630 --> 00:36:43,880
and create an illness

880
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:45,280
to treat, right?

881
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,280
Then you should change the sign outside.

882
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,000
Add the words: Wellness Center.

883
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:54,550
That changes everything.

884
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:57,320
Then, you can treat anything, right?

885
00:36:58,110 --> 00:36:59,920
You're quite a genius.

886
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:01,710
Why do all these geniuses

887
00:37:01,710 --> 00:37:03,400
end up in our small clinic?

888
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:06,480
And you're so excited?

889
00:37:06,630 --> 00:37:08,360
How dare you earn dirty money?

890
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:10,640
No.

891
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:13,200
Don't mess around.

892
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,150
That's not my idea.

893
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:14,990
We'd get bad karma.

894
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:17,090
Just do our job.

895
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:18,190
Dirty money?

896
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:19,030
Nonsense.

897
00:37:19,590 --> 00:37:20,760
I was talking about wellness

898
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,480
and health care. What are you saying?

899
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:36,510
You must be tired.

900
00:37:37,510 --> 00:37:38,960
You've lost weight again.

901
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,150
It's peak season for bookings right now.

902
00:37:42,670 --> 00:37:44,590
The Hu Xian Jie rehearsals can't stop.

903
00:37:46,110 --> 00:37:48,190
I perform out of town every few days

904
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:50,030
for three to five days at a time.

905
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:51,800
I have no time to rest.

906
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,190
How do you handle it?

907
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:55,400
I completely understand.

908
00:37:56,150 --> 00:37:58,630
Promoting a star is like Xuan paper.

909
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:01,190
A drop of ink spreads everywhere.

910
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,880
Once the paper is laid out,

911
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,030
the ink can't stop flowing.

912
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:09,880
You can't eat or drink when performing.

913
00:38:10,670 --> 00:38:12,320
You really need someone by your side.

914
00:38:12,320 --> 00:38:14,280
Luckily, Hongbing is always around.

915
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,670
He has nothing to do with me.

916
00:38:17,510 --> 00:38:18,760
How can you say that?

917
00:38:20,150 --> 00:38:21,880
Not just the provincial troupe.

918
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:22,960
Even in Diaojia Village,

919
00:38:23,190 --> 00:38:24,880
everyone knows you two are together.

920
00:38:26,510 --> 00:38:27,760
What are you thinking?

921
00:38:31,190 --> 00:38:32,440
I'm asking you.

922
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:37,510
Can my hair be washed now?

923
00:38:38,130 --> 00:38:39,000
Just a minute.

924
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,230
I'll do yours after this one.

925
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,240
Okay.

926
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:44,840
Here, let me see.

927
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:46,910
Come here.

928
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,800
You look great. So beautiful.

929
00:38:51,710 --> 00:38:52,760
So do you.

930
00:38:53,070 --> 00:38:54,440
You haven't changed a bit.

931
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:56,670
I'm old. Look at these wrinkles.

932
00:38:57,030 --> 00:38:58,030
If I didn't dye my hair,

933
00:38:58,030 --> 00:38:59,840
who knows how much gray hair I'd have?

934
00:39:04,710 --> 00:39:07,440
You still haven't answered me.

935
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:08,880
What's really on your mind?

936
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:12,710
What about you and my uncle?

937
00:39:13,190 --> 00:39:14,230
Me and your uncle?

938
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:18,150
You think we can explain ourselves?

939
00:39:18,510 --> 00:39:19,350
Exactly.

940
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,630
There's a lot we can't figure out.

941
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,320
Let's just let it be.

942
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:28,510
You didn't become a leader for nothing.

943
00:39:29,110 --> 00:39:30,440
You're mature and steady.

944
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:32,320
And you make perfect sense now.

945
00:39:36,510 --> 00:39:37,350
Aunt Hua,

946
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:41,480
my current troupe needs a lead drummer.

947
00:39:41,590 --> 00:39:43,030
I want my uncle to join us.

948
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,920
Do you think that's a good idea?

949
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,110
Absolutely.

950
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:47,760
If you asked him to do something else,

951
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:48,960
he might hesitate.

952
00:39:48,980 --> 00:39:50,290
But if you ask him to play drums,

953
00:39:50,300 --> 00:39:51,840
he'll jump at the chance.

954
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,550
Just tell him later.

955
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:56,920
I can't go.

956
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,240
Why?

957
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:01,150
You just became
the branch troupe leader,

958
00:40:01,150 --> 00:40:02,920
and you're already
bringing your uncle in?

959
00:40:03,550 --> 00:40:05,920
It just gives the gossip ammunition.

960
00:40:07,510 --> 00:40:09,670
You played for You Xi Hu last time.

961
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,920
No one said a word.

962
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,120
That was different.

963
00:40:12,230 --> 00:40:14,630
The troupe asked me to help out.

964
00:40:14,630 --> 00:40:15,790
It wasn't for you personally.

965
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:21,320
Why is your eye makeup so red?

966
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:22,710
It looks like someone punched you.

967
00:40:23,670 --> 00:40:24,510
And your hair...

968
00:40:24,510 --> 00:40:25,760
Why is it like a hard shell?

969
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:26,670
What's this look?

970
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,480
You silly old man.

971
00:40:28,670 --> 00:40:30,280
This is called fashion. Got it?

972
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:32,920
Stop saying what!

973
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:35,440
You lack drive; don't hold the kid back.

974
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:36,880
Leave. You're not welcome here.

975
00:40:37,110 --> 00:40:37,990
I haven't had liangpi.

976
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,030
I didn't make any for you.

977
00:40:39,050 --> 00:40:39,800
Leave.

978
00:40:39,810 --> 00:40:40,690
Get out of here.

979
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:41,840
Go.

980
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,320
Think about what I said.

981
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:48,110
What's there to think about?

982
00:40:53,150 --> 00:40:54,320
I understand him.

983
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:57,360
Just give him some time.

984
00:40:57,550 --> 00:40:58,710
Like uncle, like nephew.

985
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,960
You always keep things to yourselves.

986
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:03,620
You've got a mind of your own.

987
00:41:16,190 --> 00:41:17,030
Hello.

988
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:18,440
What book do you want?

989
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:21,280
Any poems by Li Bai, Cui Hu,
and Li Shangyin?

990
00:41:21,550 --> 00:41:23,440
Someone just asked the exact same thing.

991
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:24,550
Let me check.

992
00:41:24,550 --> 00:41:25,390
Okay.

993
00:41:26,670 --> 00:41:27,590
We're sold out.

994
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,150
The last book on Tang Poetry

995
00:41:29,150 --> 00:41:30,710
was bought by that person.

996
00:41:31,190 --> 00:41:32,670
When will it be back in stock?

997
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:34,280
Not until next month.

998
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,400
Check back later.

999
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:36,430
Okay.

1000
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:37,440
Check out something else.

1001
00:41:37,540 --> 00:41:42,300
(Xinhua Bookstore)

1002
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:48,710
Xue Guisheng.

1003
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:51,150
Troupe Leader Yi.

1004
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,650
Are you waiting for the bus too?

1005
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:54,400
I'm reading here.

1006
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:56,780
What book has you so hooked?

1007
00:41:56,790 --> 00:41:58,530
(Detailed Analysis of 300 Tang Poems)
Look.

1008
00:41:58,800 --> 00:41:59,880
Oh, you bought it.

1009
00:42:01,030 --> 00:42:01,870
It's nothing.

1010
00:42:03,030 --> 00:42:03,870
Well.

1011
00:42:04,190 --> 00:42:05,670
Didn't Mr. Qin say so?

1012
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:08,670
He said Hu Xian Jie has lyrics

1013
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:10,840
that are inspired

1014
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:13,920
by poems by poets like Li Bai,

1015
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,150
Li Shangyin, and Cui Hu.

1016
00:42:15,150 --> 00:42:17,710
So, I bought a copy to read

1017
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:19,760
to help me understand the lyrics better.

1018
00:42:20,190 --> 00:42:21,480
Then why are you reading it here?

1019
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:23,760
This book is 1.5 yuan.

1020
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:26,760
I just asked the cashier.

1021
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:29,190
I can return it while she's on shift.

1022
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:31,510
Her shift ends at 3:00 PM.

1023
00:42:31,510 --> 00:42:32,400
So, I decided

1024
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:33,760
to finish reading it quickly

1025
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,510
and then return it.

1026
00:42:35,630 --> 00:42:36,590
Don't return it.

1027
00:42:36,590 --> 00:42:38,110
Sell it to me when you're done.

1028
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:39,630
That doesn't seem right.

1029
00:42:39,630 --> 00:42:40,960
Why wouldn't it be?

1030
00:42:41,510 --> 00:42:43,280
If you return it,
I'll just have to buy it.

1031
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:45,190
Just sell it to me and save the trouble.

1032
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:46,160
Right?

1033
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:47,480
Take your time reading it.

1034
00:42:49,550 --> 00:42:50,390
Excuse me.

1035
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,670
Do you have the time?

1036
00:42:54,180 --> 00:42:55,120
11:30.

1037
00:42:55,150 --> 00:42:56,960
11:30? Thanks.

1038
00:42:59,190 --> 00:43:00,030
I can make it.

1039
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:02,280
By 3:00 PM,

1040
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,590
I'll give you this book.

1041
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:04,640
Okay.

1042
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

1043
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:12,080
After these performances,
I want to take a break.

1044
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:14,280
But we've committed
to the rest of the shows.

1045
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:16,480
How is the troupe
supposed to handle this?

1046
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:17,480
You even yelled at me

1047
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:18,760
over that opera wench.

1048
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:20,600
Don't you dare call her an opera wench!

1049
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:22,600
This is thrilling.

1050
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:25,040
It's the nine-tailed fox
from Zhongnan Mountain.

1051
00:43:25,720 --> 00:43:26,560
Nonsense!

1052
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:27,920
Why tear up my book?

1053
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,440
Did you cross someone?

1054
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:30,760
Qin'e, don't go there.

1055
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

1056
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

1057
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

1058
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

1059
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

1060
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

1061
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

1062
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

1063
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

1064
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

1065
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

1066
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

1067
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

1068
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

1069
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

1070
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

1071
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

1072
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

1073
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

1074
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

1075
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
